<DOC><DOCNO> AP890904-0133 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-09-04-89 2212EDT</FILEID><FIRST>u i AM-Brazil-Hostage     09-04 0226</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Brazil-Hostage,0236</SECOND><HEAD>Foiled Robber Fatally Wounded by Police, Hostage Unharmed</HEAD><HEAD>With LaserPhoto RIO2</HEAD><DATELINE>RIO DE JANEIRO, Brazil (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A robber with two revolvers whograbbed a hostage was fatally wounded in a bungled police operation,according to press accounts Monday.   Luis Fernando de Souza, who held a hotel worker hostage for morethan an hour, died at a hospital Sunday just hours after being shot,newspapers said.   Police refused comment on the reports, which were carried in mostRio dailies.   According to O Globo newspaper, Souza tried to rob the SantaComba hotel in downtown Rio but police arrived before he couldescape.   Souza then reportedly took Francisco Lima Barbosa hostage, held agun to his head and demanded police give him a getaway car.   ``The bandit was drugged and practically leaning on me. Itappeared he couldn't stand. But his finger was firmly on thetrigger,'' Barbosa said.   While a police official negotiated with Souza, two other officersquietly approached from behind, the newspaper said.   Just as one policemen prepared to tackle Souza, however, a secondfired his gun from 30 feet away, accidentally wounding anotherofficer in the leg, O Globo reported.   Souza then released his hostage and, firing his guns, tried torun to nearby hotel.   About 20 police officers opened fire as Souza fled, fatallywounding him, O Globo said.</TEXT></DOC>